v0.9.2 -- 14 March 2026 -- Updated pirate portraits (included legendary option for EM)
v0.9.1 -- 12 March 2026 -- Updated engine exhaust graphics
v0.9.0 -- 04 March 2026 -- Initial beta release

/========== What's New ==========\
- Major balance pass completed (races and components). All 46 races now have disctinct AI behaviors, ship templates, stat adjustments and diplomatic dialog.
- Fixed the "overshadow" problem with planets and shadow textures being too large
- Added the new facility "Diplomatic Center" to the game (per ExpansionMod). Diplomatic Center increases the chance for ambassadors to spawn in empire.
- Re-worked many race portraits (25 races)...some to bring them in line with Distant Worlds 2 art direction...some because I wanted to.
- Re-worked hyperdeny graphic for better visability
- Re-worked some UI elements (character icons, mainly) for better visibility

/========== Installation ==========\
1. Download and install Alvek's Expansion Mod (EM) via his Github here: https://github.com/DW-UX/DistantWorldsExpanded. Please pay attention to the instructions (especially the need to unblock the .zip before opening) to correctly install EM.
2. Download DWUR from https://github.com/salemonz/DWUR-EM.
3. Go to your Distant Worlds: Universe game folder. Then the \CUSTOMIZATION directory.
4. Unpack the folder in the downloaded DWUR archive into the CUSTOMIZATION directory.
5. Launch the game.
6. Go to "Change Theme"
7. Select DWUR-EM. (The game might hang for up to a minute while everything loads)
8. Exit the game and restart. This is important. The mod won't fully load until a game exit/restart.

/========== How to restore "Vanilla" balance ==========\
DWUR-EM has implemented a comprehensive balance pass across all 46 races. Policies, race stats, component access, ship templates, even dialog has all been edited and/or changed to make every race in DWUR feel distinct.

If you do NOT like these changes, you can restore the "vanilla" balance of old versions of DWUR.

1. Go to the \Docs folder within the mod files.
2. Open the "DWUR RESTORE VANILLA BALANCE" archive file.
3. Save the included files into your mod base folder (not the game folder...your mod folder). Overwrite when asked.